{
  "title": "VimFu \u2014 The Useless _ Key",
  "description": "The underscore key moves to the first non-blank character of the current line, just like ^. It's a candidate for remapping.",
  "speed": 0.55,
  "rows": 20,
  "cols": 40,
  "humanize": 0.7,
  "seed": 629,
  "ttsVoice": "echo",
  "playlist": "VimFu",
  "tags": [
    "vim",
    "neovim",
    "nvim",
    "vimfu",
    "tutorial",
    "terminal",
    "editor",
    "coding",
    "programming",
    "practical"
  ],
  "setup": [
    {
      "comment": "Set TERM for proper color support in Neovim"
    },
    {
      "line": "export TERM=xterm-256color"
    },
    {
      "comment": "Prepare workspace"
    },
    {
      "line": "mkdir -p ~/vimfu && cd ~/vimfu"
    },
    {
      "line": "rm -f indent.py .indent.py.swp .indent.py.swo"
    },
    {
      "line": "find ~/.local/state/nvim/swap -mindepth 1 -delete 2>/dev/null"
    },
    {
      "comment": "Create demo file"
    },
    {
      "writeFile": "indent.py",
      "content": "def greet():\n    name = \"world\"\n    print(f\"hello {name}\")\n    return True"
    },
    {
      "line": "clear"
    },
    {
      "comment": "Launch nvim"
    },
    {
      "line": "nvim indent.py"
    },
    {
      "waitForScreen": "All",
      "timeout": 30.0
    },
    {
      "ifScreen": "swap file",
      "thenKeys": "d"
    }
  ],
  "steps": [
    {
      "overlay": "VimFu",
      "caption": "The Useless _ Key",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.5
    },
    {
      "say": "The underscore key moves to the first non-blank character of the current line. Sound familiar? That's exactly what caret does."
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "say": "Move to the end of line two.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keys": "j$"
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "say": "Now press underscore.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keys": "_",
      "overlay": "first non-blank"
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.5
    },
    {
      "say": "It jumped to the N in name, skipping the spaces. Now press caret.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keys": "$"
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keys": "^",
      "overlay": "first non-blank"
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.5
    },
    {
      "say": "Same spot. Underscore and caret do the same thing on the current line. Since caret already exists, underscore is redundant."
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "say": "That makes underscore a free key to remap. Some people map it to something useful like toggling a file explorer or switching buffers."
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "say": "With a count like 3 underscore it moves down two lines to the first non-blank. But caret and plus already cover that. Remap it!"
    },
    {
      "wait": 1.0
    }
  ],
  "teardown": [
    {
      "comment": "Quit nvim without saving"
    },
    "escape",
    {
      "type": ":q!"
    },
    "enter",
    {
      "comment": "Clean up"
    },
    {
      "line": "rm -f indent.py"
    }
  ]
}
